docs.abstract: The president has lavished praise on Mohammed bin Salman, who has rapidly consolidated his position as Saudi Arabia’s heir apparent.
docs.snippet: The president has lavished praise on Mohammed bin Salman, who has rapidly consolidated his position as Saudi Arabia’s heir apparent.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump welcomed Saudi Arabia’s crown prince, Mohammed bin Salman, to the White House on Tuesday, reaffirming his embrace of an ambitious young monarch bent on reforming his country and realigning the Middle East.

headline.main: Saudi Prince’s White House Visit Reinforces Trump’s Commitment to Heir Apparent
headline.print_headline: Saudi Prince’s Visit Deepens Trump’s Commitment to Heir Apparent

docs.abstract: Justice Sotomayor issued an impassioned dissent, saying the majority had told officers that they can “shoot first and think later.”
docs.snippet: Justice Sotomayor issued an impassioned dissent, saying the majority had told officers that they can “shoot first and think later.”
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Supreme Court on Monday ruled for an Arizona police officer who shot a woman outside her home in Tucson. The court’s decision was unsigned and issued without full briefing and oral argument, an indication that the majority found the case to be easy.

headline.main: Supreme Court Rules for Police Officer in Excessive Force Case
headline.print_headline: Supreme Court Sides With Police Officer Accused of Using Excessive Force

docs.abstract: “It’s time to act,” said Kirstjen Nielsen, the secretary of homeland security, as she outlined the policy during a White House briefing.
docs.snippet: “It’s time to act,” said Kirstjen Nielsen, the secretary of homeland security, as she outlined the policy during a White House briefing.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump will issue a proclamation on Wednesday directing the Department of Defense and the Department of Homeland Security to work with governors to deploy National Guard troops to the southwest border to assist the Border Patrol in combating illegal immigration.

headline.main: Trump Will Work With Governors to Deploy National Guard to the Border

byline.original: By Julie Hirschfeld Davis and Katie Rogers

docs.abstract: The Trump administration, carrying out sanctions pressed by Congress for election interference, announced new penalties against Russia’s richest men.
docs.snippet: The Trump administration, carrying out sanctions pressed by Congress for election interference, announced new penalties against Russia’s richest men.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration imposed new sanctions on seven of Russia’s richest men and 17 top government officials on Friday in the latest effort to punish President Vladimir V. Putin’s inner circle for interference in the 2016 election and other Russian aggressions.

headline.main: Trump Administration Imposes New Sanctions on Putin Cronies
headline.print_headline: U.S. Puts New Sanctions On Putin’s Inner Circle

docs.abstract: Democrats, for their part, huddled behind closed doors to plot possible responses in case the president moved to dismiss the special counsel or the deputy attorney general.
docs.snippet: Democrats, for their part, huddled behind closed doors to plot possible responses in case the president moved to dismiss the special counsel or the deputy attorney general.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Leading congressional Republicans, confronting escalating tensions over the special counsel’s investigation, used some of the harshest language yet on Tuesday to warn President Trump against moving to undercut it. But they again stopped short of endorsing legislation to preemptively protect the special counsel, Robert S. Mueller III.

headline.main: Republicans Offer Tough Talk, but No Action, on Setting Safeguards for Mueller
headline.print_headline: Tough Talk, but No Action, on Setting Safeguards for the Special Counsel

docs.abstract: The departure of Mr. Bossert coincided with the arrival of John R. Bolton as the president’s national security adviser.
docs.snippet: The departure of Mr. Bossert coincided with the arrival of John R. Bolton as the president’s national security adviser.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A day after John R. Bolton went to work as national security adviser, he began shaking up the Trump administration’s national security ranks, ousting President Trump’s chief adviser on homeland security, Thomas P. Bossert.

headline.main: Thomas Bossert, Trump’s Chief Adviser on Homeland Security, Is Forced Out
headline.print_headline: Top Trump Homeland Security Adviser Is Forced Out as Bolton Settles In

docs.abstract: The speaker’s departure was no surprise, but the timing of it could create problems for the Republicans left behind.
docs.snippet: The speaker’s departure was no surprise, but the timing of it could create problems for the Republicans left behind.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House speakers historically exit amid political intrigue, mounting scandal or humiliating rejection by the voters. By contrast, Paul D. Ryan’s disclosure on Wednesday that he would step aside at the end of the year was quite calm and businesslike even as he gave that most Washington of reasons — more time with the family.

headline.main: A House (and a Party) Upended as Paul Ryan Calmly Takes His Leave
headline.print_headline: House (and a Party) Upended as Speaker Calmly Takes His Leave

docs.abstract: A day after announcing his retirement, Speaker Paul D. Ryan appeared to back his second-in-command, Kevin McCarthy, to succeed him, but that may not prevent an unruly fight.
docs.snippet: A day after announcing his retirement, Speaker Paul D. Ryan appeared to back his second-in-command, Kevin McCarthy, to succeed him, but that may not prevent an unruly fight.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — One day after he stunned fellow Republicans by announcing his retirement, Speaker Paul D. Ryan moved on Thursday to tamp down a succession fight, throwing his weight behind his second-in-command, Representative Kevin McCarthy of California.

headline.main: Ryan Tries to Ensure Orderly Succession, but Unrest Simmers
headline.print_headline: Ryan Seeks Orderly Succession as Unrest Stews

docs.abstract: Career diplomats have greeted the nomination of Mike Pompeo as the next secretary of state as a harbinger of new life for the department.
docs.snippet: Career diplomats have greeted the nomination of Mike Pompeo as the next secretary of state as a harbinger of new life for the department.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The calls were placed quietly to top American diplomats who had resigned in droves over the past year. The message: Mike Pompeo, nominated to become the next secretary of state, wanted them back.

headline.main: Pompeo Vows to Embrace Diplomacy, but Pledges Tougher Line on Russia
headline.print_headline: Pompeo Begins Charm Offensive Before His Senate Questioning

docs.abstract: The new Congressional Budget Office analysis, which includes the cost of the Republican tax cuts, projects the national debt to reach a level economists say could court a crisis.
docs.snippet: The new Congressional Budget Office analysis, which includes the cost of the Republican tax cuts, projects the national debt to reach a level economists say could court a crisis.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The federal government’s annual budget deficit is set to widen significantly in the next few years, and is expected to top $1 trillion in 2020 despite healthy economic growth, according to new projections from the nonpartisan Congressional Budget Office released Monday.

headline.main: Federal Budget Deficit Projected to Soar to Over $1 Trillion in 2020
headline.print_headline: Poised to Balloon to $1 Trillion,  U.S. Deficit Fuels Fear of Crisis
